    "body": "Here's a technical bugaboo: CASPER validators must have static validating code so that bets are verifiable on an absolute level. Because of this, a pool's multisig (assuming that's the most likely way to work these things) must remain constant from the moment of its creation. Because of _that_, there's no way for members to easily enter or leave, without completely rebuilding the pool.  \n",
