    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Maybe there is a workaround for this, via loading up a staking pool smart contract with participants _before it goes live_, then locking it down so it's ready to enter a validator cycle. Then have the _existing live pools expire_ / release deposits and earnings after a certain period of time, and the new ready and waiting pool takes it's place...having no more than 1 pool _fully loaded up and locked in_ waiting to go live, and 1 additional pool _actively still loading up_ with participants (and locking in when the other pool goes live as a validator). \n",
